  "excerpt": "<p>DataTools Pro Dictionary provides Salesforce object exploration. By design, the object exploration is designed for fast access to the most important object views aligned to your business.</p>",
  "content_html": "\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-container gb-block-container\"><div class=\"gb-container-inside\"><div class=\"gb-container-content\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-columns gb-layout-columns-1 one-column\"><div class=\"gb-layout-column-wrap gb-block-layout-column-gap-2 gb-is-responsive-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<p><a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/salesforce-dictionary-app/\" title=\"Free Smart Salesforce Dictionary Data Tools\">DataTools Dictionary</a> provides Salesforce object exploration for your data dictionary. By design, the object management is designed for fast access to the most important <a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/data-tools-erd-and-object-views/\" title=\"Data Tools Object and ERD Views\">object views</a> aligned to your business.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f9fbfa\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f9fbfa;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"239\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-53-1024x239.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11138 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-53-1024x239.webp 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-53-300x70.webp 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-53-768x179.webp 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-53-1536x358.webp 1536w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-53-2048x477.webp 2048w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to Access the Object Dictionary:</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When logging into DataTools Pro, by default, you will see the object dictionary. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<div class=\"ratio ratio-16x9\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"DataTools Pro Object Dictionary for Salesforce\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/V_WCCDRU7W0?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"addobjectstomigration\">Adding Salesforce Objects to your Dictionary</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>1. For DataTools Pro admin users, click on &#8220;Select Objects&#8221; button or click anywhere in the Saleseforce objects space to view a dropdown for all salesforce objects. If you do not see &#8220;Your Salesforce Objects&#8221; make sure &#8220;Show Objects is Checked&#8221;. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Note:</em></strong> The option to add more objects is not available for viewer accounts.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"153\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/image-6-1024x153.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-8762\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/image-6-1024x153.png 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/image-6-300x45.png 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/image-6-768x115.png 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/image-6-1536x229.png 1536w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/image-6-2048x305.png 2048w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Select the object/ Objects by checking the box next to the object name. You can search for specific objects by Label or API name.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"726\" height=\"484\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/image-7.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-8763\" style=\"width:275px;height:183px\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/image-7.png 726w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/image-7-300x200.png 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/image-7-600x400.png 600w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 726px) 100vw, 726px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Adding Notes and Descriptions</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>By clicking on the &#8220;Edit&#8221; button you can add notes for any object that are persisted for all users. We ae looking for feedback on notes and chat as part of data object activity management. Feel free to reach out to our team and share your needs for object management.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Notes</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Notes are currently formatted as a simple single entry text field. In the event you are using DataTools Pro to help with migration, development or other initiatives, this is an area to quickly capture basic notes.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Description</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Enter a simple description that highlights the function for your object.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Other Fields</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Have other fields that you want to organize or enhance your data dictionary? Feel free to contact our support team and we are always here to take enhancement requests!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading objectviz\">Visualize Object Relationships</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In the object manager, you can click on the diagram icon to view an interactive of the object and its direct related foreign objects. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f8fafa\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"368\" height=\"145\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-49-png.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11134 not-transparent\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f8fafa; width:240px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-49-png.webp 368w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-49-300x118.webp 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 368px) 100vw, 368px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f9fbfa\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f9fbfa;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"409\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-50-1024x409.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11135 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-50-1024x409.webp 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-50-300x120.webp 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-50-768x307.webp 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-50-1536x614.webp 1536w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-50-2048x818.webp 2048w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Adding missing objects</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When a forieng object is related but not yet added to the DataTools Pro dictionary, it is displayed as a gray entity. You can click on the &#8220;+&#8221; button to add the entity to your dictionary.</p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Creating an entity relationship diagram (ERD) View</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Clicking on &#8220;Add an ERD View&#8221; allows you to save an ERD view for easy reference and further customization. This is a great starting point to construct views that are aligned to apps, or models for analytics. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Export Object Names</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f1f9f7\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"458\" height=\"115\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-52-png.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11137 not-transparent\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f1f9f7; width:258px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-52-png.webp 458w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-52-300x75.webp 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 458px) 100vw, 458px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To quickly export a list of objects within your dictionary, you can use our available export options</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Copy to clipboard</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Export to CSV </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Export to Excel</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Categorizing and Grouping Objects in Views</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To organize objects together in one or multiple views, you can click the &#8220;Edit Views&#8221; button.  <br><a href=\"https://datatoolspro.com/tutorials/data-tools-erd-and-object-views/\" title=\"Data Tools Object and ERD Views\"><strong>Learn More about Views</strong></a></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"552\" height=\"266\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-42.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-9192\" style=\"width:435px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-42.png 552w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-42-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 552px) 100vw, 552px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Managing Fields</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f5faf8\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"914\" height=\"354\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-51-png.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-11136 not-transparent\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f5faf8; width:545px;height:auto\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-51-png.webp 914w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-51-300x116.webp 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/image-51-768x297.webp 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 914px) 100vw, 914px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>To view individual fields within each object, simply click on the object name within the object table.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"/salesforce-field-dictionary-with-datatools-pro/\" title=\"View and Manage Fields Documentation\"><strong>View and Manage Fields Documentation</strong></a></p>\n</div></div>\n</div></div>\n</div></div></div>\n"
}